Northstar linux is an experimental linux distribution based on sabotage[1]
linux. Using musl[2] libc, northstar build an entire userspace statically,
simplifying many aspects of the system.

The package system is based on Slackware[3]'s SlackBuild scripts and
driven by mk and utility scripts.

Bootstrap instructions:
$ cp dist/bootstrap.config config
$ . config
$ mk install-bootstrap

[1] http://github.com/chneukirchen/sabotage
    http://github.com/rofl0r/sabotage
[2] http://www.etalabs.net/musl
[3] http://www.slackware.com/
